With the exception of the skin of the injection site and in the underlying muscle, vaccine plasmids were readily cleared from the majority of organs (Table 2
). At day 40 we detected plasmid in the spleen of the analyzed animal and by day 60 post immunization we could detect low levels of plasmid in the lungs of the analyzed animal (Table 2). At day 120 post immunization the plasmid DNA vaccine had been cleared from all organs except skin of the injection sites (Table 2, Fig. 2
). The level of plasmids at the injection site decreased substantially over time but at the end of the experiment, at day 120 post immunization, several thousand copies of plasmid/μg of extracted DNA still remained.
